{
  "video_id": "s4smjT1qwZU",
  "title": "Carl Schoonover: How to look inside the brain",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 15619.0,
      "end_time": 19615.0,
      "text": "This is a thousand-year-old drawing of the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 19615.0,
      "end_time": 21526.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a diagram of the visual system."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21527.0,
      "end_time": 24277.0,
      "text": "And some things look very familiar today."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24277.0,
      "end_time": 28644.0,
      "text": "Two eyes at the bottom, optic nerve flowing out from the back."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 28644.0,
      "end_time": 30764.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a very large nose"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 30764.0,
      "end_time": 34810.0,
      "text": "that doesn&#39;t seem to be connected to anything in particular."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 34810.0,
      "end_time": 35781.0,
      "text": "And if we compare this"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35781.0,
      "end_time": 37855.0,
      "text": "to more recent representations of the visual system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 37855.0,
      "end_time": 40812.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ll see that things have gotten substantially more complicated"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40812.0,
      "end_time": 42385.0,
      "text": "over the intervening thousand years."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 42385.0,
      "end_time": 45349.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s because today we can see what&#39;s inside of the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 45350.0,
      "end_time": 47831.0,
      "text": "rather than just looking at its overall shape."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 47831.0,
      "end_time": 51810.0,
      "text": "Imagine you wanted to understand how a computer works"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 51810.0,
      "end_time": 54989.0,
      "text": "and all you could see was a keyboard, a mouse, a screen."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 54989.0,
      "end_time": 57385.0,
      "text": "You really would be kind of out of luck."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 57385.0,
      "end_time": 59427.0,
      "text": "You want to be able to open it up, crack it open,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 59427.0,
      "end_time": 61271.0,
      "text": "look at the wiring inside."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61271.0,
      "end_time": 63135.0,
      "text": "And up until a little more than a century ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63135.0,
      "end_time": 65134.0,
      "text": "nobody was able to do that with the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65135.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67150.00000000001,
      "text": "Nobody had had a glimpse of the brain&#39;s wiring."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 67150.0,
      "end_time": 69967.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s because if you take a brain out of the skull"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 69967.0,
      "end_time": 71656.0,
      "text": "and you cut a thin slice of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 71656.0,
      "end_time": 74154.0,
      "text": "put it under even a very powerful microscope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 74154.0,
      "end_time": 75335.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s nothing there."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 75335.0,
      "end_time": 76948.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s gray, formless."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 76948.0,
      "end_time": 79551.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s no structure. It won&#39;t tell you anything."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 79552.0,
      "end_time": 82406.0,
      "text": "And this all changed in the late 19th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 82406.0,
      "end_time": 86281.0,
      "text": "Suddenly, new chemical stains for brain tissue were developed"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 86281.0,
      "end_time": 89930.0,
      "text": "and they gave us our first glimpses at brain wiring."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 89930.0,
      "end_time": 91106.0,
      "text": "The computer was cracked open."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 91106.0,
      "end_time": 93961.0,
      "text": "So what really launched modern neuroscience"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 93962.0,
      "end_time": 95927.0,
      "text": "was a stain called the Golgi stain."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 95927.0,
      "end_time": 97808.0,
      "text": "And it works in a very particular way."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 97808.0,
      "end_time": 100918.0,
      "text": "Instead of staining all of the cells inside of a tissue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 100918.0,
      "end_time": 103950.0,
      "text": "it somehow only stains about one percent of them."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 103950.0,
      "end_time": 107292.0,
      "text": "It clears the forest, reveals the trees inside."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 107292.0,
      "end_time": 109964.0,
      "text": "If everything had been labeled, nothing would have been visible."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 109964.0,
      "end_time": 112100.0,
      "text": "So somehow it shows what&#39;s there."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 112100.0,
      "end_time": 114677.0,
      "text": "Spanish neuroanatomist Santiago Ramon y Cajal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 114677.0,
      "end_time": 117522.0,
      "text": "who&#39;s widely considered the father of modern neuroscience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 117522.0,
      "end_time": 121419.0,
      "text": "applied this Golgi stain, which yields data which looks like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 121419.0,
      "end_time": 125176.0,
      "text": "and really gave us the modern notion of the nerve cell, the neuron."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 125177.0,
      "end_time": 127791.0,
      "text": "And if you&#39;re thinking of the brain as a computer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 127791.0,
      "end_time": 129801.0,
      "text": "this is the transistor."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 129800.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131876.0,
      "text": "And very quickly Cajal realized"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 131877.0,
      "end_time": 134214.0,
      "text": "that neurons don&#39;t operate alone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 134214.0,
      "end_time": 136520.0,
      "text": "but rather make connections with others"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 136520.0,
      "end_time": 138558.0,
      "text": "that form circuits just like in a computer."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 138558.0,
      "end_time": 141948.0,
      "text": "Today, a century later, when researchers want to visualize neurons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 141949.0,
      "end_time": 144716.0,
      "text": "they light them up from the inside rather than darkening them."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 144716.0,
      "end_time": 145866.0,
      "text": "And there&#39;s several ways of doing this."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 145866.0,
      "end_time": 147593.0,
      "text": "But one of the most popular ones"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 147593.0,
      "end_time": 149685.0,
      "text": "involves green fluorescent protein."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 149685.0,
      "end_time": 151344.0,
      "text": "Now green fluorescent protein,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 151344.0,
      "end_time": 154489.0,
      "text": "which oddly enough comes from a bioluminescent jellyfish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 154489.0,
      "end_time": 155727.0,
      "text": "is very useful."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 155727.0,
      "end_time": 158365.0,
      "text": "Because if you can get the gene for green fluorescent protein"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 158365.0,
      "end_time": 160400.0,
      "text": "and deliver it to a cell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 160400.0,
      "end_time": 161787.0,
      "text": "that cell will glow green --"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 161787.0,
      "end_time": 165533.0,
      "text": "or any of the many variants now of green fluorescent protein,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 165533.0,
      "end_time": 167196.0,
      "text": "you get a cell to glow many different colors."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 167197.0,
      "end_time": 168718.0,
      "text": "And so coming back to the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 168718.0,
      "end_time": 172518.0,
      "text": "this is from a genetically engineered mouse called \"Brainbow.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 172518.0,
      "end_time": 174680.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s so called, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 174680.0,
      "end_time": 177680.0,
      "text": "because all of these neurons are glowing different colors."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 177680.0,
      "end_time": 181131.0,
      "text": "Now sometimes neuroscientists need to identify"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 181131.0,
      "end_time": 184175.0,
      "text": "individual molecular components of neurons, molecules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 184175.0,
      "end_time": 185973.0,
      "text": "rather than the entire cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 185973.0,
      "end_time": 187679.0,
      "text": "And there&#39;s several ways of doing this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 187679.0,
      "end_time": 189148.0,
      "text": "but one of the most popular ones"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 189148.0,
      "end_time": 191343.0,
      "text": "involves using antibodies."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 191343.0,
      "end_time": 192679.0,
      "text": "And you&#39;re familiar, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 192680.0,
      "end_time": 195631.0,
      "text": "with antibodies as the henchmen of the immune system."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 195631.0,
      "end_time": 198490.0,
      "text": "But it turns out that they&#39;re so useful to the immune system"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 198490.0,
      "end_time": 200599.0,
      "text": "because they can recognize specific molecules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 200599.0,
      "end_time": 202718.0,
      "text": "like, for example, the coat protein"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 202718.0,
      "end_time": 205106.0,
      "text": "of a virus that&#39;s invading the body."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 205106.0,
      "end_time": 207150.0,
      "text": "And researchers have used this fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 207151.0,
      "end_time": 211476.0,
      "text": "in order to recognize specific molecules inside of the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 211476.0,
      "end_time": 214116.0,
      "text": "recognize specific substructures of the cell"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 214116.0,
      "end_time": 216360.0,
      "text": "and identify them individually."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 216360.0,
      "end_time": 219385.0,
      "text": "And a lot of the images I&#39;ve been showing you here are very beautiful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 219385.0,
      "end_time": 221291.0,
      "text": "but they&#39;re also very powerful."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 221291.0,
      "end_time": 222927.0,
      "text": "They have great explanatory power."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 222927.0,
      "end_time": 225170.0,
      "text": "This, for example, is an antibody staining"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 225170.0,
      "end_time": 228537.0,
      "text": "against serotonin transporters in a slice of mouse brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 228537.0,
      "end_time": 230218.0,
      "text": "And you&#39;ve heard of serotonin, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 230218.0,
      "end_time": 233450.0,
      "text": "in the context of diseases like depression and anxiety."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 233450.0,
      "end_time": 234452.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ve heard of SSRIs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 234453.0,
      "end_time": 237350.0,
      "text": "which are drugs that are used to treat these diseases."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 237350.0,
      "end_time": 240239.0,
      "text": "And in order to understand how serotonin works,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 240240.0,
      "end_time": 243316.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s critical to understand where the serontonin machinery is."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 243316.0,
      "end_time": 244912.0,
      "text": "And antibody stainings like this one"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 244912.0,
      "end_time": 248458.0,
      "text": "can be used to understand that sort of question."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 248458.0,
      "end_time": 251160.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d like to leave you with the following thought:"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 251160.0,
      "end_time": 253626.0,
      "text": "Green fluorescent protein and antibodies"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 253626.0,
      "end_time": 256632.0,
      "text": "are both totally natural products at the get-go."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 256632.0,
      "end_time": 259411.0,
      "text": "They were evolved by nature"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 259411.0,
      "end_time": 261978.0,
      "text": "in order to get a jellyfish to glow green for whatever reason,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 261978.0,
      "end_time": 266361.0,
      "text": "or in order to detect the coat protein of an invading virus, for example."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 266362.0,
      "end_time": 269379.0,
      "text": "And only much later did scientists come onto the scene"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 269379.0,
      "end_time": 271402.0,
      "text": "and say, \"Hey, these are tools,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 271402.0,
      "end_time": 273515.0,
      "text": "these are functions that we could use"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 273515.0,
      "end_time": 275522.0,
      "text": "in our own research tool palette.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 275523.0,
      "end_time": 279151.0,
      "text": "And instead of applying feeble human minds"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 279151.0,
      "end_time": 281350.0,
      "text": "to designing these tools from scratch,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 281350.0,
      "end_time": 283939.0,
      "text": "there were these ready-made solutions right out there in nature"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 283939.0,
      "end_time": 287175.0,
      "text": "developed and refined steadily for millions of years"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 287175.0,
      "end_time": 288875.0,
      "text": "by the greatest engineer of all."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 288875.0,
      "end_time": 290137.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 290137.0,
      "end_time": 292675.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}